            <paragraph>Called when the engine determines whether this <strong>MovieWriter</strong> is able to handle the file at <literal>path</literal>. Must return <literal>true</literal> if this <strong>MovieWriter</strong> is able to handle the given file path, <literal>false</literal> otherwise. Typically, <reference internal="True" refid="class-moviewriter-private-method-handles-file"><inline classes="std std-ref">_handles_file()</inline></reference> is overridden as follows to allow the user to record a file at any path with a given file extension:</paragraph>
            <literal_block force="False" language="gdscript" linenos="False" xml:space="preserve">func _handles_file(path):
